## Evidence factors — Bug Validation (Rule 32)

Base: **40**

| Factor | Points | Condition | Weight rationale |
|--------|--------|-----------|-----------------|
| Phoenix code read + cited (file:line) | **+20** | Step 4 completed with ≥1 code citation | Runtime verification (Rule QA.0 dual-track) |
| Confluence evidence found (exact or contextual match) | **+15** | Step 2 returned ≥1 relevant page with title+ID+URL | Documented product intent; essential for mismatch detection |
| Swagger/OpenAPI aligned (after refresh) | **+10** | Step 3 completed; spec confirms or contradicts reporter claim | Contract-level; less authoritative than code for runtime behavior |
| DB evidence gathered (same env) | **+10** | Step 4b completed with ≥1 query result | Supporting evidence; confirms data state but not behavior rules |
| Environment aligned (PHOENIX-SWITCH.0) | **+5** | Step 0.1 exit code 0 | Prerequisite; low weight because it's binary pass/fail |
| User requirements clear (ticket has steps + expected) | **+5** | Step 1 extracted from ticket text (not inferred) | Reduces ambiguity but doesn't add technical evidence |
| Diagram evidence used | **+3** | Step 1b matched ≥1 diagram | Supplementary; never overrides code/Confluence |
| Confluence exact match (not just contextual) | **+5** | Bonus on top of +15 above | Exact match is stronger than contextual |
| Swagger refresh failed (using cached) | **-10** | Script exit ≠ 0; cached spec used | Stale spec may have wrong fields/enums — significant risk |
| No Confluence found | **-10** | Step 2 returned 0 relevant pages | Missing secondary source |
| DB query failed | **-5** | Step 4b query error or connection failure | Supporting evidence missing, not primary |
| Assumption made (per assumption) | **-5** | Each inferred behavior not backed by evidence | Each assumption is a potential error |
| Phase 2 exclusion applied (Prod/PreProd) | **-5** | Some wiki pages excluded from decision basis | Narrower evidence base |
| Single evidence source only | **-15** | Only code OR only Confluence — not both | Cross-validation impossible; high risk |
| Mismatch documented as Finding (Rule QA.2; both sides cited) | **+10** | Code↔Doc or Swagger↔Code conflict surfaced | Product-quality deliverable |
| Conflict present but not reported as Finding | **-15** | Violates Rule QA.0 |
| Environment alignment partial (exit code 2) | **-5** | Mixed-state repos | Some repos may be on wrong branch |

**Max achievable:** 40 + 73 = 113 → capped at **100**

