## Evidence factors — Regression Validation (Dev-to-Dev2)

Base: **40** (applied to **each** sub-score: Dev sub-score and Dev2 sub-score independently).

**Aggregation:** `Final = MIN(Dev sub-score, Dev2 sub-score)` — same minimum-of-critical as HandsOff.

**Mutually exclusive groups:** factors marked `[GROUP X]` — apply **only one** from each group per sub-score. Applying multiple from the same group is a scoring error.

### Dev sub-score factors (Steps 0-3)

| Factor | Points | Condition | Group |
|--------|--------|-----------|-------|
| Jira ticket fetched + rich data (desc + AC) | **+20** | Step 1a: description + acceptance criteria present | `[A]` |
| Jira ticket fetched + sparse (summary only) | **+10** | Step 1a: minimal detail | `[A]` |
| Both MCP and REST Jira failed | **-20** | Step 1: PROCESS BLOCKED | `[A]` |
| Git commit found referencing ticket | **+10** | Step 1b: `git log --grep` returned results | — |
| Dev environment aligned (exit 0) | **+5** | Step 2a: full success | `[B]` |
| Dev alignment partial (exit 2) | **-5** | Step 2a: some repos misaligned | `[B]` |
| Dev code found + cited (file:line) | **+15** | Step 2c: relevant implementation located | `[C]` |
| No code found for ticket scope | **-15** | Steps 1-2: CODE_MAPPING = UNKNOWN | `[C]` |
| Dev code matches Jira description | **+10** | Step 3: code clearly addresses ticket | `[D]` |
| Dev code partially matches | **+5** | Step 3: some aspects unclear | `[D]` |
| Dev code does not match ticket description | **-10** | Step 3: unclear alignment | `[D]` |
| Assumption made (per assumption) | **-5** | Any inferred behavior | — |
| Step Validator critical failure | **-10** | Wrong branch, PROCESS BLOCKED recovered | — |
| Step Validator minor failure | **-3** | HEAD not fresh, non-critical warning | — |

### Dev2 sub-score factors (Steps 4-5)

| Factor | Points | Condition | Group |
|--------|--------|-----------|-------|
| Jira ticket quality (inherited from Dev) | **+20 or +10** | Same as Dev `[A]` result | `[A]` |
| Dev2 environment aligned (exit 0) | **+5** | Step 4a: full success | `[E]` |
| Dev2 alignment partial (exit 2) | **-5** | Step 4a: some repos misaligned | `[E]` |
| Ticket commit found on Dev2 | **+15** | Step 4c: `git log origin/dev2 --grep` found it | `[F]` |
| Ticket commit NOT on Dev2 | **-15** | Step 4c: not deployed | `[F]` |
| Dev2 code matches Dev for ticket scope | **+15** | Step 5: `git diff` shows no relevant differences | `[G]` |
| Dev2 code partially matches | **+5** | Step 5: some changes present, some missing | `[G]` |
| Significant Dev vs Dev2 differences | **-10** | Step 5: unexpected code divergence | `[G]` |
| Code missing entirely on Dev2 | **-20** | Step 5: file or method absent | `[G]` |
| Mismatch documented as Finding | **+5** | Senior QA Finding filed per Rule QA.2 | — |
| Mismatch present but no Finding | **-10** | Mismatch detected but not documented | — |
| Assumption made (per assumption) | **-5** | Any inferred behavior | — |
| Step Validator critical failure | **-10** | Wrong branch, PROCESS BLOCKED recovered | — |
| Step Validator minor failure | **-3** | HEAD not fresh, non-critical warning | — |

**Max achievable per sub-score:** 40 + 60 = **100** (with perfect evidence on all groups).

**Three-Zone meaning for regression:**

| Zone | Range | Interpretation |
|------|-------|---------------|
| **GO** | ≥ 85% | Code deployed and verified on Dev2 — high confidence |
| **CAUTION** | 55–84% | Likely deployed but gaps exist — recommend manual spot-check |
| **STOP** | < 55% | Cannot confirm deployment — manual verification required |

**Output format:**
```
**Confidence: XX% (ZONE)** [aggregation: minimum-of-subscores]
- Dev: XX% (ZONE)
- Dev2: XX% (ZONE) ← limiting factor
Reason: <which sub-score limited and why>
```

